An independent interoperability reference for Roland's REAC (EtherType 0x8819),
derived from FreeREAC's own packet captures, from GPL-3.0 open-source
reverse-engineering projects, and from a reverse-engineering pass on console
firmware — all re-expressed in FreeREAC's own words and tables. REAC is a Roland
trademark; this is not official Roland documentation, and FreeREAC is not affiliated
with or endorsed by Roland.

## References

The wire-format reference draws on three GPL-3.0 reverse-engineered codebases:

  - per-gron/reacdriver — GPL-3.0
  - norihiro/obs-h8819-source — GPL-3.0-or-later
  - norihiro/reaccapture — GPL-3.0-or-later

Protocol facts (the wire schema, message formats, the remote-control command
surface) are unprotected interface data, restated here in our own words and tables.
No Roland binaries, symbols, or decompilation listings are reproduced.
